In England, in the seven days to 02 March, there were 177,255 new confirmed cases (313.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 February, there were 200,279 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 11% (23,024 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 07 March is 16,277,054 (28,783.4 cases per 100,000 population).
